# Cursor Rules ‚Äî FOSS Boilerplate

Read `.agents/CONSTITUTION.md` first. All rules there apply here.

## Key Constraints

- Source build (`Dockerfile` / `Dockerfile.go`) is always priority over `Dockerfile.binary`
- Version format: `{upstream_version}-r{N}` ‚Äî e.g. `6.0.0-r1`, `6.0.0-r2`, `6.1.0-r1`
- Branch format: `release/6.0.0-r1`, `hotfix/6.0.0-CVE-2024-1234`, `feature/description`, `chore/description`
- Scripts stored as `.txt` in repo: `build.sh.txt`, `scan.py.txt` ‚Äî never `.sh`
- No secrets committed ‚Äî `.cicd/docker-resources/secrets/` is gitignored
- No `latest` base image tags in Dockerfiles ‚Äî always pin versions
- Every patch in `patches/` needs header: CVE, Upstream-PR, Keep-on-sync
- `.local/` for compose files + tool Dockerfiles; `.cicd/` for pipeline only ‚Äî never mix
- `.local/` compose services: `pull_policy: missing` + `image: foss-*:local` on build services
- Python tool images: `python:*-slim` + `uv` binary from `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv`
- Runtime image priority: `scratch` (static) ‚Üí `gcr.io/distroless/*` ‚Üí `*-slim` ‚Äî never full OS as runtime base; downgrade needs CHANGELOG entry
- Language auto-detect from source signals (`go.mod`‚ÜíGo, `Cargo.toml`‚ÜíRust, `CMakeLists.txt`‚ÜíC/C++, `pom.xml`‚ÜíJava, `pyproject.toml`‚ÜíPython, etc.) ‚Äî full table: CONSTITUTION ¬ßLanguage & Build Tool Detection
- Version probe: try latest stable first, step down one minor on failure, floor = upstream's minimum; never silently pin old version ‚Äî full algorithm: CONSTITUTION ¬ßProgressive Version Probe

